original_output.subject: Coffee in Boston next week?
original_output.body:
Hi Anthony,

I'll be in Boston December 14th-16th and wanted to reach out given CEO Yamani Rangan's vision of hybrid teams with people and AI agents working together.

Your engineering leadership at HubSpot—scaling product development while maintaining the innovation velocity that built the platform—puts you at the center of this transformation. The challenge most VPs face is delivering on AI promises without overwhelming existing teams or compromising quality.

Devin, the AI software engineer, has rolled out in production at [Citi](https://www.americanbanker.com/news/citi-is-rolling-out-agentic-ai-to-its-40-000-developers) and [Goldman Sachs](https://www.cnbc.com/2025/07/11/goldman-sachs-autonomous-coder-pilot-marks-major-ai-milestone.html). On average, engineering teams see 6–12x efficiency gains while freeing developers for customer-facing innovation.

Would you be open to coffee one morning? I promise it'll be more energizing than a New England road race.

Best,
Jake

improved_version:
Hi Anthony,

I’ve been cycling for the past 15 years and love the feeling of the bike tires on a trail. Saw you are quite the cyclist yourself (8th-place finish in a NE road race) -- is this still something you find yourself doing? Even when traveling I try to make sure I carve out time to run/bike. 

I’m Jake and I’m a Director here at Cognition and wanted to reach out to you based on similar orgs I’m meeting with to discuss AI agents for software development. I'll be in Boston December 14th-16th and wanted to reach out given CEO Yamani Rangan's vision of hybrid teams with people and AI agents working together.

Devin, the AI software engineer, has rolled out in production at Citi, Goldman Sachs, and Ramp among others. On average, engineering teams see 6–12x efficiency gains while freeing developers for customer-facing innovation.

Would you be open to coffee and a bike ride one morning I’m in town? 

Best,
Jake
